==English==

===Etymology===
[[Spanish]] there is ''¡[[ay]]!'' ([[interjection]] denoting [[surprise]]) and caramba is a lace worn on the head and an [[w:Euphemism|euphemism]] for [[carajo]], which in South America means [[fuck]] or [[hell]].  The phrase was popularized by it's use from [[w:Bart Simpson|Bart Simpson]] in [[w:The Simpsons|The Simpsons]].  (Note that typical English misinterpretation is much milder.)

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[&#712;ai&#124; ka.&#712;&#638;am.ba&#8214;]}}

===Phrase===
'''¡[[Ay]], [[caramba]]!'''

# ''(euphemistic):'' [[Oh]] [[crap]]!

